Pege 64,1. 5. Hugo de courtenay. His age is here a little exaggerated. He was born in 1275, became 5th baron Courtenay in 1291, was summoned to parliament 5th Feb. 1299, was created oerl of Devon 22nd Feb. 1335, and died before January, 1341. As chief commissioner of array for coS. Cornwall, Devon, Somerset, and Dorset, he would take command of the forces which repelled the French attack.-—See Doyle‚ Baranage, i. 574.
